		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_QANAT_STRATEGY">
			<Text>The Qanat is a Classical-era building which increases a Desert City's Growth by enhances Desert tiles. May only be built on or next to a Desert and next to a source of fresh water. Being an underground structure it is also immune to nukes and collateral damage.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_QANAT_PEDIA">
			<Text>A Qanat is a series of well-like vertical shafts, connected by gently sloping tunnels and create a reliable supply of water for human settlements and irrigation in hot, arid, and semi-arid climates. The Qanat technology is known to have been developed by the Persian people sometime in the early 1st millennium BC and spread from there slowly westward and eastward.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]--Wikipedia</Text>
		</Row>
